--------------------------------------------------------    Phase 1 - Abstract    --------------------------------------------------------------------

- Phase 1 of the ULTIMA 2.0 Project consists of the creation of the Scheduler and Semaphore for our operating system. These
components provide the operating system with the ability to manage processes/threads, synchronize shared resources (like the screen), 
and see the status of active processes/threads. A process/thread can have any of the 4 states: "running", "blocked", "ready", or "dead". 
The process scheduler is displayed as a table that shows the following fields for all active tasks: Task Name, TaskID, State, etc.
The scheduler uses its own dynamic thread table (linked list of Task Control Blocks (TCB)) to preserve these states and will be used to 
maintain other information in the future.
The binary semaphore implemented acts as a lock for shared resources where:     if (semaphore_value == 0), the resources are locked
                                                                                if (sempahore_value == 1), resources are free to be used
